data.value:
1. Connect the circuit in wye-wye configuration as shown in the Figure at the discussion. a. Connect first the terminal H1 of transformer 1 to terminal (red) of primary line A. Then, connect the terminal H2 of transformer 1 to terminal (black) of primary line N. Second, connect the terminal X1 of transformer 1 to terminal (red) of secondary line L1. Then, connect the terminal X2 of transformer 1 to terminal (black) of the secondary line N. For transformer 2, connect first the terminal H1 of transformer 2 to terminal (blue) of primary line B. Then, connect the terminal H2 of transformer 2 to terminal (black) of primary line N. Second, connect the terminal X1 of transformer 2 to terminal (blue) of secondary line L2. Then, connect the terminal X2 of transformer 2 to terminal (black) of the secondary line N. For transformer 3, connect first the terminal H1 of transformer 3 to terminal (yellow) of primary line c. Then, connect the terminal H2 of transformer 3 to terminal (black) of primary line N. Second, connect the terminal X1 of transformer 3 to terminal (yellow) of secondary line L3. Then, connect the terminal X2 of transformer 3 to terminal (black) of the secondary line N.
b. For the load, connect terminal (red) of Load 1 to terminal (red) of L1 in secondary side. Then connect terminal (black) of Load 1 to terminal (black) of secondary line N. Next connect terminal (red) of Load 2 to terminal (blue) of secondary line L2. Then, connect terminal (black) of load 2 to terminal (black) of secondary line N. Next connect terminal (red) of Load 3 to terminal (yellow) of secondary line L3. Then, connect terminal (black) of load 3 to terminal (black) of secondary line N.
2. Measure the voltage and current in primary side or source side of the transformer. a. For phase voltage, connect the terminal (red) of voltmeter to the terminal H1 of transformer 1. Then, terminal (black) of voltmeter to terminal H2 of transformer 1. Turn on the switch, measure and record the line to line voltage reading. Turn off the switch and return to the original connection. b. For line to line voltage, connect the terminal (red) of voltmeter to the terminal H1 of transformer 1. Then, terminal (black) of voltmeter to terminal H1 of the transformer 2. Turn on the switch, measure and record the line to line voltage reading. Turn off the switch and return to the original connection. c. For line to line current, connect the terminal (red) of clamp meter to the terminal (red) of digital ammeter. Then, terminal (black) of clamp meter to terminal (black) of digital ammeter. Use the clamp meter to measure the line to line current in line H1 of transformer 1. Clamp it on line H1 of transformer 1 and line A. Turn on the switch, measure and record the line to line current reading. Turn off the switch and return to the original connection. d. For Phase current, no need to measure the phase current in wye – wye connection because in wye connection Phase current and Line current are equal.
3. Measure the voltage and current in secondary side or load side of the transformer.
a. For phase voltage, connect the terminal (red) of voltmeter to the terminal X1 of transformer 1. Then, terminal (black) of voltmeter to terminal X2 of transformer 1. Turn on the switch, measure and record the phase voltage reading. Turn off the switch and return to the original connection. b. For line to line voltage, connect the terminal (red) of voltmeter to the terminal X1 of transformer 1. Then, terminal (black) of voltmeter to terminal X1 of the transformer 2. Turn on the switch, measure and record the line to line voltage reading. Turn off the switch and return to the original connection. For phase current, connect the terminal X1 and terminal X2 of transformer 1. Then connect the terminal (red) of clamp meter to the terminal (red) of digital ammeter. Then, terminal (black) of clamp meter to terminal (black) of digital ammeter. Use the clamp meter to measure the phase current in transformer 1. Clamp it on line X1 and X2 of transformer 1. Turn on the switch, measure and record the phase current reading. Turn off the switch and return to the original connection. c. For line to line current, connect the terminal (red) of clamp meter to the terminal (red) of digital ammeter. Then, terminal (black) of clamp meter to terminal (black) of digital ammeter. Use the clamp meter to measure the line to line current in line X1 of transformer 1. Clamp it on line X1 of transformer 1 and line L1. Turn on the switch, measure and record the line to line current reading. Turn off the switch and return to the original connection. d. For Phase current, no need to measure for the phase current in wye – wye connection because in wye connection Phase current and Line current are equal.
